nc:Case.nc:CaseTitleText: Sinkfield. v. HUD, No. 10-885, 2012 U.S. Dist. LEXIS 35233, at *13-15 (S.D. Ohio Mar. 15, 2012); Hornbostel v. U.S. Dept. of the Interior, 305 F.Supp.2d 21, 30 (D.D.C. 2003), summary affirmance granted, No. 03-5257, 2004 WL 1900562 (D.C. Cir. Aug. 25, 2004).

foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The pending value for OGC should have been 143 last year to reflect one request counted as pending which was actually closed. There were also 5 pending requests for OIG that were inadvertently left off the count for last year.

foia:OldestPendingAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The requester was contacted and she agreed to a rolling production for the responsive documents.

foia:SimpleResponseTimeIncrementsSection.foia:FootnoteText: OIG requests were placed in the complex track.

foia:ComplexResponseTimeIncrementsSectio.foia:FootnoteText: The combination of the simple and complex tracks totals 306 requests.

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: OIG had one request for expedited processing which was adjudicated in 10 days.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: While OIG had 3 requests pending at the end of the fiscal year, the due dates for all of the requests were for the new fiscal year.
